understand
how and why cannabis works in
our bodies.

39:51.022 --> 39:54.392 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then, in the early '90s, he
had a eureka
moment.

39:54.425 --> 40:01.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. RAPHAEL MECHOULAM: THC
mimics compounds
which we make called endogenous
cannabinoids,

40:01.499 --> 40:07.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
which our brain makes, our body
makes. THC
mimics their effects. All this
is called the

40:07.305 --> 40:13.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
endocannabinoid system, and this
endocannabinoid
system seems to be extremely
important.

40:13.411 --> 40:17.715 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Here's how
endocannabinoids
works in our nervous system.

40:17.749 --> 40:23.154 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The nerves that form the
electrical grid of
our body are not continuous
strands of fiber.

40:23.187 --> 40:29.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Instead, there are many gaps in
the wiring.
The nerve ends are called
neurons, the gaps,

40:29.360 --> 40:35.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
synapses. The electrical current
is transmitted
from neuron to neuron across
synapses by chemical

40:35.600 --> 40:38.536 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
messengers called
neurotransmitters.

40:38.569 --> 40:43.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The volume and route of these
signals determines
what we are thinking, what we
perceive and

40:43.574 --> 40:51.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what we feel. Our body generates
cannabinoids
to help regulate the flow of
these neurotransmitters.

40:51.783 --> 40:56.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Scientists suspect the active
ingredient in
cannabis, THC, can either can
increase or

40:56.888 --> 41:02.660 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
decrease the flow of the
neurotransmitters.
And this can have all kinds of
impacts on

41:02.694 --> 41:04.462 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
our physical state of being.

41:04.495 --> 41:09.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. RAPHAEL MECHOULAM: The
endocannabinoid
system is involved in
essentially all human

41:09.901 --> 41:11.736 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
diseases.

41:11.769 --> 41:16.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: Different
endocannabanoid receptors
are found in non-nerve cells in
the immune

41:16.140 --> 41:21.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
system, for example. So perhaps
it is no surprise
that researchers suspect
cannabis can do so

41:21.746 --> 41:27.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
many things, from fighting
cancer, to concussions,
to Crohn's disease.

41:27.752 --> 41:34.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But perhaps the most dramatic
story of how
cannabis might be good medicine
is in epilepsy.

41:34.492 --> 41:41.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the '70s and '80s, Dr.
Mechoulam published
studies that showed CBD can curb
seizures.

41:41.899 --> 41:46.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was no further research,
until parents
of epileptic children who didn't
respond to

41:46.938 --> 41:50.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conventional pharmaceuticals
discovered Dr.
Mechoulam's work.

41:50.575 --> 41:53.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CATHERINE JACOBSON,
Neuroscientist: I do this
with two hats.

41:53.644 --> 41:58.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Neuroscientist
Catherine Jacobson
told her story to the cannabis
medical conference

41:58.416 --> 42:08.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at Harvard. Her 7-year-old son,
Ben, has epilepsy.
After discovering Dr.
Mechoulam's papers,

42:08.760 --> 42:14.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
